The paper proposes a new language for knowledge compilation called ROBDD with implied literals, which is relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses algorithms and implementation, which are related to data structures (cs.DS) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the paper deals with logical operations and querying requirements, which are relevant to data mining (cs.DM).
